 One person had to be cut free with the Jaws of Life, after a collision between a bakkie and truck on the N11, Van der Stel Rd, at Van Riebeeck Park turn off, on Friday morning, 27 October. Public Safety officers, fire department, SharajEMS, InnovaMed, KZNEMS and ER24 Ladysmith were called at the scene. The entrapped driver had to be cut free from the mangled wreck. It is not clear what the cause of the accident was and police will be investigating it. The injured were removed andÂ stabilised before being taking to the hospital. 